result.execSummary:
The defendant Bobby R Buechel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing hearing on February 13, 2017 at 09:30 am.

Def in person & by Atty Mike Kenitz.  Atty Sandra Jo Giernoth appeared for State.  Clerk: CP.  DAY 1 OF 2.  Case called 8:19am w/out jury.  Statements from State and counsel.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present at 8:43am.  Jury sworn before voir dire.  20 jurors called to box.  Voir dire by Court.  Voir dire by counsel.  Jurors struck by counsel.  12 juror names called.  Remaining jurors thanked and released at 9:30am.  Jury excused.  Recess.  Reconvene w/out jury present.  Atty Kenitz motions for sequestration; Court so orders.  Jury present.  Court gives preliminary instructions to jury.  Opening statements.  WITNESS:  Lynn H.  Sidebar w/Court and counsel.  WITNESSES:  Lynn H. (continued); Russ R.; Officer J. Krick (HPD).  Sidebar w/Court and counsel.  WITNESSES:  Officer J. Krick (continued); Sgt T. Hayes (HPD).  State plays video; State/counsel agree court reporter does not need to take down.  Jury admonished and excused for lunch.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  WITNESS:  Sgt T. Hayes (continued); Officer T. Fassbender (HPD).  State rests.  Jury excused.  Recess.  Reconvene.  Def will not be testifying. Court questions def and finds def is exercising his right to remain silent.  Atty Kenitz motions for dismissal; Court denies.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  Def rests.  Closing arguments.  Court reads instructions to jury.  Bailiff sworn.  Jury excused for deliberations at 2:54pm.  Recess.  Reconvene w/jury present.  Court reads verdicts.  Jury finds def guilty of Ct 1, guilty of Ct 2, guilty of Ct 3, guilty of Ct 4.  Jury polled.  Jurors thanked and released at 3:29pm.  State moves for judgment on verdicts; Court grants.  Court sets separate sentencing date.  Court admonishes def re terms of bond.  Day 2 of jury trial removed from calendar.  Case closed 3:31pm.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for February 13, 2017 at 09:30 am.
